When we execute the call to the presigned URL
```commandline
$ curl https://k3#####ia.execute-api.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/api/presignedurl?mail=eduard@orkei.com
```

Whe receive a json response as follows:
```json
{
  "url": "https://s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/videos.oico.com",
  "fields": {
    "acl": "public-read",
    "key": "79c8dc#####71e4b.mp4",
    "AWSAccessKeyId": "ASIAY###4CH7K6J6",
    "x-amz-security-token": "IQoJb3JpZ##########",
    "policy": "eyJleHBpcmF################",
    "signature": "ZEzZZao#######GYiE2mTgM="
  }
}
```

And with this response we can upload a video file, for example an intro.mp4:
```commandline
$ curl -X POST  -F "acl=public-read" \
     -F "key=79c8dcb651f5b7071e4b.mp4" \
     -F "AWSAccessKeyId=ASIAYTMWOMLF4CH7K6J6" \
     -F "x-amz-security-" \
     -F "" \
     -F "signature=ZEzZZao7UFO1QRVV22GYiE2mTgM=" \
     -F "file=@intro.mp4" https://s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/videos.oico.com
```
